      "structure_id": "fraction_compare_half_mcq",
      "topic": "fractions",
      "section": "A",
      "marks": 2,
      "text": "Which of the following fractions is greater than 1/2?",
      "options": ["2/5", "3/7", "4/8", "5/9"],
      "correct_option": 3,
      "answer": "5/9",
      "working": "5/9: compare 5×2 vs 9×1 → 10 > 9, so 5/9 > 1/2. Check others: 2/5: 10 vs 10 → equal to 4/10 = 2/5 < 1/2. 3/7: 6 < 7. 4/8 = 1/2 exactly.",
      "source": "ACS Junior 2025 WA3 Q4"
    },
    {
      "structure_id": "missing_fraction_to_one_mcq",
      "topic": "fractions",
      "section": "A",
      "marks": 2,
      "text": "What is the missing fraction in the box?\n6/10 + ___ = 1",
      "options": ["2/5", "3/5", "4/5", "6/10"],
      "correct_option": 0,
      "answer": "2/5",
      "working": "1 - 6/10 = 4/10 = 2/5",
      "source": "ACS Junior 2025 WA3 Q5"
    },
    {
      "structure_id": "fraction_comparison_true_mcq",
      "topic": "fractions",
      "section": "A",
      "marks": 2,
      "text": "Which of the following is true?",
      "options": ["2/9 > 5/9", "5/6 < 2/3", "1/8 > 1/11", "3/4 = 6/12"],
      "correct_option": 2,
      "answer": "1/8 > 1/11",
      "working": "Same numerator: smaller denominator = larger fraction. 8 < 11, so 1/8 > 1/11. Check others: 2/9 < 5/9 (same denominator). 5/6 > 2/3 = 4/6. 3/4 ≠ 6/12 = 1/2.",
      "source": "ACS Junior 2025 WA3 Q6"
    },
    {
      "structure_id": "ordering_fractions_short",
      "topic": "fractions",
      "section": "B",
      "marks": 2,
      "text": "Arrange the following fractions in order. Begin with the greatest.\n3/8,  1/4,  5/10",
      "options": null,
      "correct_option": null,
      "answer": "5/10, 3/8, 1/4",
      "working": "Convert to common denominator (40): 5/10=20/40, 3/8=15/40, 1/4=10/40. Order greatest first: 20/40, 15/40, 10/40 → 5/10, 3/8, 1/4",
      "source": "ACS Junior 2025 WA3 Q9"
